The system would be used by the manager, owner and the supplier of the stock.

1) The stock management system allows the manager to record information of the items available in the store and generate reports based on the total amount of sales. 
2) The stock management system allows the owner to sell/order the stalk.
3) It also allows the owner to report quality issues, track orders, make payments etc.
4) It also allows the supplier to supply the stocks and see the orders place to them as well as the track the orders out for delivery.
5) The system retains the records of the cost, expiry date, vendor details, discount and quantity.
